# Solution

The problem "Length of Last Word" asks us to find the length of the last word in a given string. A word in this context is defined as a maximal substring consisting of non-space characters only.

For example, consider the string "Hello World". The last word in this string is "World", and its length is 5.

**Time complexity :** **O(n)**
**Space complexity :** **O(1)**
```C++ []
class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLastWord(string s) {
        int res = 0;
        for (int i = s.length()-1; i >= 0;) {
            // Check if the current character is not a space
            if (s[i--] != ' ')
                res++; // Increment the length of the last word
            else if (res > 0)
                return res; // Return the length if a space is encountered after counting some characters
        }
        return res; // Return the length of the last word
    }
};
```
