# **Java Solution:**
```
class Solution {
    public int lengthOfLastWord(String s) {
        // Initialize length...
        int length = 0;
        // Create a loop starting from last character...
        for (int i = s.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            // If the character is not a space...
            if (s.charAt(i) != ' ') {
                length++;
            }
            // Here it is the end of last word...
            else if(length != 0) {
                break;
            }
        }
        return length;
    }
}
```

# **C++ Solution:**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLastWord(string s) {
        // base case...
        if(s.length()<1)
            return 0;
        int end = s.length() - 1;
        // Find first character from the end
        while (end >= 0 && s[end] == ' ')
            --end;
        const int beg = end;
        // Find first space from the last character
        while (end >= 0 && s[end] != ' ')
            --end;
        return beg - end;     //return the length...
    }
};
```

# **Python Solution:**
```
class Solution(object):
    def lengthOfLastWord(self, s):
        s = s.strip()       # Remove the spaces at the beginning and end
        length = 0
        for i in range(len(s)):
            # Waiting for the next word...
            if s[i] == " ":
                length = 0
            else:
                length += 1    # Inside one word
        return length
```

