## **Simple Approach :**

Store **Every time**(again and again) updated Number as a string and traverse through all character of string which actually is number with storing every character into one variable then break this process when string size is only left as 1. 

Example : 
**Num = 1234**
String **s = "1234"**
int **a = 1+2+3+4** (in every turn when loop rotates.)
now **s = "10"** ( here a = 10 **number to string** once again.)
now **a = 1+0** 
**s = "1"** (s is again num to string of a  &  Here Loop Will Break Because s.size()=1)
**return s[0]-'0'** (Which Is Final Single Digit Number)

```
class Solution {
public:
    int addDigits(int num) {
        string s = to_string(num);
        int a = 0;
        while(s.size()!=1){
            for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); ++i)
            {
                a = a + (s[i]-'0');
            }
            s = to_string(a);
            a = 0;
        }
        return s[0]-'0';
    }
};
```


