class Solution {
public:
    int addDigits(int n) {
        int sum = 0; // declare sum as zero

        while(n > 0) // until our number is greater than zero
        {
            sum += n % 10; // add last digit to our sum

            // it is same as applying function again as in the recursion
            // So suppose, if number is 19, then when we do 19 % 10 it gives us 9
            // & 19 / 10 it gives us 1
            // and if we add them we got 9 + 1 i.e 10
            // so, at this point, our sum again becomes 10, and we always know that
            // sum will be always two digit, therefore, why not add digits of sum.
            // Therefore, 10 % 10 = 0 & 10 / 10 = 1 (it is not biwise and) I m just writing and
            // 0 + 1 = 1 that is our sum becomes 1 and which is correct answer, 
            // i hope u got this

            sum = (sum % 10 + sum / 10); 

            n = n / 10; // divide n by 10 
        }

        return sum; // and at last return sum
    }
};
```
