**As ,**
1 % 9 = 1
10 % 9 = 1
100 % 9 = 1
 so ..`10^n ≡ 1 (mod 9)`, 
 and thus **a<sub>n</sub>10^n + a<sub>n-1</sub>10^n + ... + a<sub>1</sub>10 + a<sub>0</sub> ≡ a<sub>n</sub> + ... +a<sub>0</sub> (mod 9)**
this process can be continued until a number less than 9 is gotten, i.e. num % 9.
