This is the Brute force approach.
Add the Digits of the number till the number become less than equal to 9*/
```
class Solution {
public:
    int addDigits(int num) {
        while(true)
        {
            int sum=0;
            while(num>0)
            {
                sum=sum+num%10;
                num=num/10;
            }
            if(sum<=9)
                return sum;
            num=sum;
        }
        return 0;
    }
};
```
/*Daily Challenge:-08/02/2022.
**Method2:-Follow up of this question. O(1) time**
-->The sum of digits untill we reach single digit is called **Digit Root**.
-->**For any base B and and a number N of that base.**
The Digit root(Db) in that base is define as below formula:-
**Db(N)=0 ,if N==0.
Db(N)=1+(N-1)mod(B-1),if N!=0.**
For proof Visit:-https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_root
T.C=O(1).*/
