solutions.content:
**
**BRUTE FORCE APPROACH**

**EXPLANATION** : FIND THE SUM OF DIGITS UNTIL IT IS LARGER THAN 9 i.e NOT A SINGLE DIGIT
**

```
class Solution {
    public int addDigits(int num) 
    {
		int t=num;
        int sum=0;
        while(t>9)
        {
            while(t>0)
            {
                int r = t%10;
                sum+=r;
                t=t/10;  
            }
            t=sum;
            sum=0;           
        }
        return t;
		}
	}
```

**
LETS OPTIMIZE THIS WITH THE HELP OF **%** OPERATOR 

**EXPLANATION**: IF num IS 0 RETURN IT. 
IF THE MOD OF NUM BY 9 IS 0 THEN RETURN 9  BECAUSE THE SUM OF DIGITS WILL ALWAYS BE 9. 
ELSE RETURN num%9
**

```
class Solution {
    public int addDigits(int num) 
    {
	if(num==0) return 0;
        if(num%9==0) return 9;
        return num%9;
	}
}
```

