We note that the answer is basically num % 9 for all numbers except for those divisible by 9 (e.g, 18, 36,189 etc.) For these numbers, num % 9 will incorrectly yield 0. However, if we subtract 1 from these numbers (num - 1) % 9 will be 8. So, 1 + (num - 1) % 9 gives us the correct result, 9.

Similarly, it can be easily proved that, for other numbers for which num % 9 = x (where 1 <= x <= 8), (num-1) % 9 will always be x - 1. So, the answer is again 1 + (num - 1) % 9. Finally, for num = 0, (num - 1) % 9 = -1, so 1 + (num - 1) % 9 = 0. Therefore, we can write the code unconditionally like below:

