# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int addDigits(int num) {

        //if the number is less than or equal to 9, return it as it cannot be reduced further
        if(num <= 9){
            return num;
        }

        // while the number is greater than 9, keep adding its digits until it reduces to a single digit
        while(num > 9){
            int ans = 0; // initialize a variable to store the sum of the digits

            // add up the digits of the current number
            while(num > 0){
                int rem = num % 10; // get the last digit of the number
                ans = ans + rem; // add the last digit to the sum
                num = num / 10; // remove the last digit from the number
            }

            num = ans; // assign the sum to the number for the next iteration of the loop
        }

        // return the single digit number
        return num;
    }
}

```

