var addDigits = function(num) {
    if(num<=9) return num
 return num%9===0?9:num%9
};

Any number divided by 9 always gives sum of all the digits or 0( which means it is a multiple of 9, which would give 9 on adding the digits) as reminder

If num == 0 -> ans = 0

If num % 9 == 0 -> ans = 9

If num % 9 != 0 ->
num = nearest multiple of 9 which is less than num + (num % 9)
So, ans = (9 + (num % 9)) % 10
Here, 9 + (num % 9) will always be 2 digit number. (because num % 9 != 0)
First digit will always be 1. And 2nd will be (num % 9) - 1
So, sum = (num % 9)

